<div data-en>

<h2 class="section-title">A Brief Introduction</h2>

<p>Hi, I'm <strong>Albert Wang</strong>, a Computer Science student at <strong>Feng Chia University</strong> in Taiwan.
I'm passionate about <strong>embedded systems, cloud and edge computing, and AI-driven system integration</strong>, and I enjoy building systems that truly work from the ground up.</p>

<p>I currently work as a <strong>System Engineer</strong> at <a href="https://imcloud.co/" target="_blank"><strong>imCloud Co., Ltd.</strong></a>,
which is <strong>Feng Chia University's fourth spin-off company</strong>, originated from the <strong>Intelligent Machines and Systems Laboratory (IMSL)</strong>.
The company and lab were founded by <strong>Prof. Yuan-Jen Chang</strong>, who previously served as a visiting scholar at the <a href="https://researchdirectory.uc.edu/facilities/85" target="_blank"><strong>Center for Intelligent Maintenance Systems (IMS)</strong></a> at the <strong>University of Cincinnati</strong>, led by <strong>Prof. Jay Lee</strong>.
After returning to Taiwan, Prof. Chang introduced advanced <strong>Predictive Health Management (PHM)</strong> and <strong>smart maintenance</strong> technologies, which became the foundation for establishing both IMSL and imCloud.
My current work focuses on <strong>software development, sensor data acquisition, PHM applications</strong>, and <strong>AWS Greengrass Core (GGC)</strong> services,
where I build <strong>data ingestion pipelines, device control logic, and IoT edge collaboration systems</strong>.</p>

<p>Outside of work, I actively explore various <strong>side projects</strong>, especially with <strong>Raspberry Pi</strong> and <strong>ESP32</strong>.
I'm a dedicated <strong>DietPi</strong> user, often experimenting with lightweight systems for server deployment, automation, and edge computing integration.</p>

<p>I'm also preparing for my next academic step — pursuing a <strong>master's degree abroad</strong> in <strong>Canada</strong> or the <strong>United States</strong>,
focusing on <strong>AI, data analytics, and predictive maintenance (PHM)</strong>.
To achieve that, I'm improving my English proficiency, aiming to reach <strong>IELTS 6 / CEFR B2</strong> within a year.</p>

<p>Beyond programming, I'm passionate about <strong>flight simulation (VATSIM Callsign: EVA431)</strong>, <strong>photography</strong>, and <strong>amateur radio communication (BX7ADG)</strong>.</p>

<p>I'm also building my personal brand <strong>Prisvalis</strong>, with the domain <a href="https://prisvalis.com" target="_blank"><strong>prisvalis.com</strong></a>.
Although it's still in its early stage, my goal is to turn it into a platform that integrates <strong>AI, data, and automation</strong>,
developing technologies that truly make a difference in everyday life.</p>

